cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper is about evaluating models of situated language understanding, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses neural networks and machine learning, which are relevant to cs.LG (Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of a grid world suggests a connection to robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
